            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "@justinmk  I only knew about this in the context of Node.js, so I looked into it. Since this is about `ts_ls`, researching TypeScript and tsgo should be sufficient.\r\n\r\n- Node.js: https://nodejs.org/api/modules.html#loading-from-node_modules-folders\r\n- TypeScript: https://www.typescriptlang.org/docs/handbook/modules/reference.html#node_modules-package-lookups\r\n  - There were other module resolution methods before TS 6.0, but in my experience, I have never seen any projects using that version that also use this option.\r\n    - 6.0 release note: https://www.typescriptlang.org/docs/handbook/release-notes/typescript-6-0.html#deprecated---moduleresolution-classic\r\n  - It was thought that tsgo would not change because it is a line-to-line port, but I am providing the source just in case.\r\n    - https://github.com/microsoft/typescript-go/blob/0a7c6b47e6163892880e0e5814e519c435445f11/internal/module/resolver.go#L1003-L1016",
